renderer = extract_ptr(r&quot;hint=(0x[0-9a-fA-F]+)&quot;, receipt)
From earlier:

replay leaks fx_draw_basic
receipt leaks puVar14 (heap object)

So we can compute:
pie_base = fx_draw_basic - 0x2260
win = pie_base + 0x2460

Note on add_order 12 1
The choice of (12, 1) is intentional, but not needed to understand this step yet.
It will be explained later when we discuss how to control the write primitive from reroute.





                  Step 2 — The Main Constraint in reroute



The tricky part is that reroute does not give a fully controlled 8-byte write.
Relevant code:
piVar21 = (int *)(lVar30 + (long)iVar25 * 8);
piVar21[1] = iVar27;
*piVar21 = iVar20 + iVar6;
So the write is split like this:
[0..3] = order_y * G + order_x
[4..7] = 3rd argument of reroute
That means:

upper 4 bytes are fully controlled from reroute
lower 4 bytes come from the coordinates we chose in add_order

So we cannot just freely write any 8-byte pointer in one shot.





                  Step 3 — Exploit Strategy 



Our goal is to overwrite:
heap + 0x430   // fx_finish_dummy

